  "reasoning": "The nfs3_rpc_wrapper function contains a logic error in its JUKEBOX retry handling. The function unconditionally sets res = -ERESTARTSYS (error -512) at line 39 after every sleep for a JUKEBOX retry, before checking if a signal is actually pending at line 40. This causes the function to return -512 even when the RPC response was successful or when no signal actually interrupted the sleep. The correct behavior should be to only set res = -ERESTARTSYS if a fatal signal is actually detected, not unconditionally before the signal check. This bug manifests when NFS revalidation is triggered during mount expiration in autofs, causing NFS mounts to disappear with 'getattr failed, error=-512' instead of properly completing the revalidation. The issue is a regression between kernel 3.14.12 (which worked) and 4.1.15 (broken), likely due to changes in how the freezable scheduler or signal handling interacts with the JUKEBOX retry logic."
}

